Fix checks that are still failing
commitResults.messageBody:
Checks are failing because the valid data files used for testing got
cleared during testing. Current workaround is to set a flag and check
if a test is being performed, to prevent the files from being cleared.
This is likely going to be a temporary solution.

Previously all read and write operations were done in one class.
